briefdescription.para: A macro for wrapping the return type of the swizzled method.
A macro for wrapping arguments of the swizzled method.
A macro for wrapping the replacement code for the swizzled method.

detaileddescription.para: A macro for casting and calling original implementation. May be used only in RSSwizzleInstanceMethod or RSSwizzleClassMethod macros.
Swizzles the instance method of the class with the new implementation.

Swizzling frequently goes along with checking whether this particular class (or one of its superclasses) has been already swizzled. Here the RSSwizzleMode and key parameters can help. See +[RSSwizzle swizzleInstanceMethod:inClass:newImpFactory:mode:key:] for details.

parameterdescription.para: The class with the method that should be swizzled.
Selector of the method that should be swizzled.
The return type of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWReturnType macro.
The arguments of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWArguments macro.
The code of the new implementation of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWReplacement macro.
The mode is used in combination with the key to indicate whether the swizzling should be done for the given class. You can pass 0 for RSSwizzleModeAlways.
The key is used in combination with the mode to indicate whether the swizzling should be done for the given class. May be NULL if the mode is RSSwizzleModeAlways.

simplesect.para: YES if successfully swizzled and NO if swizzling has been already done for given key and class (or one of superclasses, depends on the mode).

detaileddescription.para: Swizzles the class method of the class with the new implementation.

parameterdescription.para: The class with the method that should be swizzled.
Selector of the method that should be swizzled.
The return type of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWReturnType macro.
The arguments of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWArguments macro.
The code of the new implementation of the swizzled method wrapped in the RSSWReplacement macro.

memberdef.name: _RSSwizzleInstanceMethod
memberdef.initializer: [RSSwizzle \ swizzleInstanceMethod:selector \ inClass:[classToSwizzle class] \ newImpFactory:^id(RSSwizzleInfo *swizzleInfo) { \ RSSWReturnType (*originalImplementation_)(_RSSWDel3Arg(__unsafe_unretained id, \ SEL, \ RSSWArguments)); \ SEL selector_ = selector; \ return ^RSSWReturnType (_RSSWDel2Arg(__unsafe_unretained id self, \ RSSWArguments)) \ { \ RSSWReplacement \ }; \ } \ mode:RSSwizzleMode \ key:KEY];

memberdef.name: _RSSwizzleClassMethod
memberdef.initializer: [RSSwizzle \ swizzleClassMethod:selector \ inClass:[classToSwizzle class] \ newImpFactory:^id(RSSwizzleInfo *swizzleInfo) { \ RSSWReturnType (*originalImplementation_)(_RSSWDel3Arg(__unsafe_unretained id, \ SEL, \ RSSWArguments)); \ SEL selector_ = selector; \ return ^RSSWReturnType (_RSSWDel2Arg(__unsafe_unretained id self, \ RSSWArguments)) \ { \ RSSWReplacement \ }; \ }];

detaileddescription.para: A function pointer to the original implementation of the swizzled method.
A factory block returning the block for the new implementation of the swizzled method.
You must always obtain original implementation with swizzleInfo and call it from the new implementation.

parameterdescription.para: An info used to get and call the original implementation of the swizzled method.

simplesect.para: A block that implements a method. Its signature should be: method_return_type ^(id self, method_args...). The selector is not available as a parameter to this block.

inbodydescription.para: RSSwizzle does not do swizzling if the same class has been swizzled earlier with the same key.

RSSwizzle does not do swizzling if the same class or one of its superclasses have been swizzled earlier with the same key.
There is no guarantee that your implementation will be called only once per method call. If the order of swizzling is: first inherited class, second superclass, then both swizzlings will be done and the new implementation will be called twice.
